Appendix C: Essentials of Free Probability

C.1 Free Cumulants and $R$-Transform

Let $(\mathcal{M}, \tau)$ be a tracial non-commutative probability space. For a random variable $X$, the free cumulants $\kappa_n$ are defined implicitly by
\tau(X^n) = \sum_{\pi \in NC(n)} \prod_{V \in \pi} \kappa_{|V|}(X),


where $NC(n)$ is the set of non-crossing partitions of $\{1,\dots,n\}$. The $R$-transform is the formal power series
R_X(z) = \sum_{n\ge 1} \kappa_{n+1}(X) z^n.


For freely independent $X,Y$, $R_{X+Y}(z) = R_X(z) + R_Y(z)$.

C.2 Free Fisher Information

For a self-adjoint $X$, the conjugate variable $\xi$ (if it exists) satisfies
\tau(\xi P(X)) = \tau( \partial_X P(X) )


for all polynomials $P$, where $\partial_X$ is the free difference quotient defined by
\partial_X(P(X)) = \frac{P(X) - P(Y)}{X - Y}


evaluated in the limit $Y \to X$. The free Fisher information is $\Phi^*(X) = \tau(\xi^2)$. For semicircular variables, $\Phi^* = 1$.

C.3 Free Entropy

The microstates free entropy of $X$ is
\chi(X) = \iint \log |s-t| d\mu_X(s) d\mu_X(t) + \frac{3}{4},


where $\mu_X$ is the spectral distribution. The non-microstates free entropy is defined via the conjugate variable. The free log-Sobolev inequality links free entropy and free Fisher information.

